# 🚀 Using Flex System on Page – CSS Basics

## 📌 Overview

This project marks the **beginning of my CSS journey**.

It is a static webpage where I applied **Flexbox** to layout elements efficiently, along with **shadows** and **hover effects** to enhance the visual design.

🔗 **Live Demo:**  
https://abdelrahmangalal200101-cpu.github.io/Using-Flex-System-On-Page/

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- HTML5  
- CSS3  
- Flexbox layout  
- Box-shadow & Hover effects  

---

## 🎯 What I Learned

- Using Flexbox for responsive layouts  
- Applying shadows to elements for depth  
- Using hover states for interactive UI  
- Combining CSS properties to create visually appealing pages  
- Structuring CSS cleanly for maintainability  

---

## 📈 Progress Note

This project shows the next step after basic HTML tables.  

It reflects my **growth in styling and layout techniques**, moving from plain static structures to responsive and interactive designs.

It laid the foundation for building more dynamic and visually polished pages in future projects.
